  "pride_metadata": {
    "project": {
      "accession": "PXD030600",
      "title": "Secretome Analysis of Pseudoalteromonas flavipulchra DSM 14401",
      "additionalAttributes": [],
      "projectDescription": "Crystalline chitin is a kind of high molecular-weight polymers which is difficult to degrade. N-acetylglucosamine and chitooligosaccharides (COSs) are important agriculture, medicine, cosmetics and food resources. Conversion of crystalline chitin to GlcNAc and COSs using recombinant chitinases is an environmentally compatible, reproducible and products controllable method. Here, we report the ability of Pseudoalteromonas flavipulchra DSM 14401 to degrade crystalline.",
      "sampleProcessingProtocol": "Strain DSM 14401 was cultured at 25\u00b0C and 180 rpm in the minimal medium supplemented with 3% flake chitin. When the chitin was about half degraded, the culture was centrifuged (8,000 rpm for 6 min at 4\u00b0C). The precipitates were resuspended using 20 mM Tris-HCl with 1M NaCl, and followed by centrifugation (3000 rpm for 3 min at 4\u00b0C). Repeat three times. The precipitates were resuspended using 50 mM Tris-HCl congtaining 6 M Guanadine-HCl, and then centrifuged (11,000 rpm for 10 min at 4\u00b0C) to get the supernatant which was subsequently moved into 3K ultrafiltration tube. The Guanadine-HCl in the supernatant was removed by adding 50 mM Tris-HCl to the ultrafiltration tube (15 mL, 3KD, 6,000 rpm for 10 min at 4\u00b0C) repeatly. Then the proteins in the supernatant were precipitated by 50 mL acetone with 10% trichloroacetic acid and 0.1% dithiothreitol overnight at -20\u00b0C. The precipitates were harvested and washed by 80% acetone and 100% acetone, and followed by lyophilization. Then, the lyophilization sample were successively denatured, reduced and alkylated by denaturation buffer (0.5 M Tris-HCl, 2.75 mM EDTA, 6 M Guanadine-HCl), dithiothreitol (1M) and iodoacetamide (1M). The sample was further replaced with 25mM NH4HCO3 solution by ultrafiltration (1 mL, 3KD, 12,000 rpm for 15 min at 4\u00b0C) and digested using trypsin (Promega) at 37\u00b0C for 12 h to collect the peptides that were further desalted on the C18 column (Millipore). The desalted protein was injected and analyzed using the mass spectrometer Orbitrap Elite (ThermoFisher Scientific, Bremen, Germany) coupled with Easy-nLC 1000 (Thermo Fisher Scientific, Bremen, Germany). Finally, the raw data was analyzed using Thermo Scientific Proteome DiscovererTM 1.4.",
      "dataProcessingProtocol": "Thermo Scientific proteome discoverer software version 1.4",
